    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1164" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄπ-ειμι</span></b>  (1), fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπεσσεῖται, ἀπέσσεται</span>, pres. subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπέῃσι</span>, ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπέην,
            ἄπεσαν</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">distant</span>)
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">from</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινός</span>),
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be absent, wanting;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τόσσον ἀπῆν ὅσον τε γέγωνε βοήσᾱς,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 5.400</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> σοὶ
            δ᾽ ὁδὸς οὐκέτι δηρὸν ἀπέσσεται</span>, ‘you shall not  have to wait much longer for the journey,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 2.285</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
